narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this class to fellow students. If you want to get an in-depth summary of slavery, this is the class.

This is a great course that traces slavery from Aristotle's idea of natural slavery to slavery in Judaism and Christianity to slavery in America. The readings were great and I came out of the class with a better understanding of the topic. It has been one of my favorite seminars. Definitely take it! Also Professor Fraistat is fabulous.
Yes, I would recommend this course for anyone who has an interest at all in slavery and the political thought around it.
